            "answer_text": "I don\u2019t speak German well, but I can say that syntax is similar, but not the same. For example, in English, I might say \u2018How much do the potatoes cost?\u2019, or simply \u2018How much are the potatoes?\u2019. If you said this with German syntax, it would be more like \u2018How much cost the potatoes?\u2019 (Wie viel kosten die kartoffeln?\u2019). You would be understood, but grammatically, it\u2019s incorrect. So, in answer, no! Edit: to reverse it, writing the German words with English syntax, we have \u2018Wie viel die kartoffeln kosten\u2019, which I believe is wrong! ",
